  "text": "THSD1 might have a role in radiation response as it was one of the consensus radiation response genes in primary human fibroblasts [CITATION_1] . The thrombospondins (TSPs) might act to support tumor progression to metastasis through their effects on the degradation of the extracellular matrix and the ability of tumor cells to invade the surrounding tissues, although few studies have addressed the role of the TSPs in metastasis in vivo (34) .",
